  "summary": "Preinstall hook exfiltrates host identifiers to attacker-controlled IP and OAST domain",
  "details": "On `npm install`, the package's preinstall lifecycle hook runs index.js, which collects host identifiers (os.hostname(), os.userInfo().username, __dirname, process.cwd()) and exfiltrates them through two channels: a DNS lookup against a hex-encoded label under `.d8jbmnsqcfu78dfs8vdg34ohqhirb4pbg.oast.live` (interactsh-style OAST exfil) and an HTTP POST to bare IP `172.201.213.59:9090/c`. The package describes itself only as 'security research' and ships no legitimate functionality. The inflated version (99.0.2) under the `@klapp-about` scope is consistent with a dependency-confusion attempt against an internal Klapp package.",
